\cf0 Shift\
\
\pard\tx566\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Shift is what really makes this module one of the best sounding ones in my opinion, it's like frequency modulation but on steroids, because it modulates the frequency of each pulsar independently with different ratios while squeezing and stretching the wavelets, when you crank up the "Amount" it warps the sound creating increasingly complex metallic sounds.\
\
Shift has two parameters:\
\
Amt - The amount of modulation for all pulsars. (the CV for this parameter is input through the last inlet - "Shift Amt".\
\
Ratio - The ratio of the modulator with the main frequency, the options are: 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1, 1.25, 1.5, 1.75, 2.\
\
The knob next to the ratio is a fine frequency control of the modulator frequency.\
\
\
The horizontal slider between the two outputs is a control for stereo width, in fact what it does is spread the 4 wavelets in the sequence across the stereo field in their order (from left to right).}